4.20	Forschungszentrum_Karlsruhe	Karlsruhe Institute of Technology	The Karlsruhe Institute of Technology is one of the largest research and educations institution in Germany, resulting from a merger of the university (Universit√§t Karlsruhe (TH)) and the research center (Forschungszentrum Karlsruhe) of the city of Karlsruhe. The university, also known as Fridericiana, was founded in 1825. In 2009, it merged with the former national nuclear research center founded in 1956 as the Kernforschungszentrum Karlsruhe (KfK). One of nine German Excellence Universities, the KIT is one of the leading universities in science and engineering in Europe, ranking 7th overall in terms of citation impact.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/Fridericiana_audimax.jpg/300px-Fridericiana_audimax.jpg
